{"hypothesis_id": "HM5", "rev": 1, "ts": "2026-05-17T18:25:00Z", "statement": "METHODOLOGY CANON (user decision 2026-05-17). DEFAULT directional training objective for ALL subsequent research = R1: XGB/logloss (or model-equivalent) with sample_weight proportional to |forward move over H|, clipped at train-p99. NOT plain logloss / NOT MSE-on-return. Justification (HR1, well-powered, both symbols x H{180,300,600}): R1 is the ONLY reward formulation uniformly >= R0 — 6/6 cells dR0>0 (+0.002..+0.020), placebo-clean; the SIGN consistency is significant (one-sided sign-test p≈0.016) even though NO single cell clears 2*SE. Mechanism is principled for a cost-floored directional problem (concentrates loss capacity on economically-decisive moves; R0/MSE squander it on untradeable sub-cost wiggles — the mild sibling of the HM2 magnitude-bias defect). BOUNDED claim: R1 is a BASELINE-OBJECTIVE upgrade, NOT a lever/alpha (does not clear the refutation bar; will not alone make a strategy). baseline_ref going forward = R1 (paired with the HA1 rank-IC anchor). R2/R3/R4 REJECTED as defaults: R2 degenerates SOL (AUC 0.500, sub-cost collapse), R3 rank:pairwise significantly NEGATIVE on SOL, R4 asym-cost null. Reversible if future evidence contradicts; until then every directional run trains & is judged under R1.", "status": "confirmed", "priority_rank": 0, "result_experiment_id": "phaseb-20260517-180221_HR1_LINK-USDT-PERP_H600", "note": "Prevents tiling the R0/MSE 'wrong-objective' defect into every future experiment (incl. the HM3 sequence path). Decisive answer to user's 'which reward point do we keep for all subsequent research'. Not an over-claim: explicitly small-effect, sign-test-justified, baseline-not-lever, reversible."}
